04/03/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- A US Justice Department official pledged Monday (3 March) to help Albanian authorities fight organised crime. Carl Alexandre, director of the Justice Department's Office of Overseas Prosecutorial Development, met with Albanian Minister of Justice Spiro Peci in Tirana. He reiterated US support for Albania's efforts against illegal trafficking. The two also discussed legislative reforms and approved documents on US technical assistance for the training of judges and prosecutors. (ATA - 03/03/03)
